NT||cp|8|AT|^B@2^Y@3^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Now, as to the play. A diamond is certainly reasonable on the auction, and I might very well have chosen it. However, it turns out that, although in general it is a bad idea to lead a suit the opponents have bid, this is one hand with a possible exception. It turns out that if declarer bids a major, and it is likely to be only 4 cards and weak and you as opening leader hold 4+ cards in that major with 2 honors  it is often right to lead that suit. So, since I am known to have 4 hearts (I opened 1N 12-14 not 1H)  and Gorrila has 2 honors in hearts, a heart lead can be considered. In this case, it works pretty well.|
