cp|8|AT|^B@2^Y@3^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Let's see if Gorrila should consider slam. He does have the following dummy points. 14 HCP, 1 quality suit and 1 doubleton = 16. So, if South has 17+ dummy points, slam is possible. Some people would consider slam, and that would not be a terrible idea. However, there are some minuses to the Gorrila's hand. First, of all, you need close to a maximum from South. Second, we only have a probable 8 card fit. On close contracts, you should tend to be conservative with an 8-card fit, more aggressive with a 9-card fit. Finally, Gorrila has kind of flat distribution. Because of those 3 factors (pard needs a max, 8-card fit, flat distribution) I would tend to be conservative.|
