st||pn||sk|E|md|3S46JH345D589TQC47,S378TH278JD4KC29T,S2QKH9TQD27AC568K,|rh||ah|Board A|ah|hondo717 mentoring session|sv|o|mb|1N|mb|p|mb|p|mb|p|lb|*CWhat would be your opening lead? The Player may not lead the same card.^^C3^sa95hak6caqj3dj63^|sk||pc|D3|cp|8|AT|^B@2^Y@3^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Let's talk about the opening lead. In general, I am a big believer in "4th from longest and strongest." Although no opening lead rule is perfect, that rule has served me well over the years. So, in this deal, I would have led a club. On a real good day, pard would have the King. But even if she does not, you will set up some club tricks. You can make a case for leading either a low club or the Queen. However, I  would lead low.|
