up||pc|c3|NT||cp|8|AT|^B@2^Y@3^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Another point on the opening lead. Leading from Jxx is usually a very weak lead. It often gives a lot away. This hand is a good example of that. No matter how the hand is defended, North has 4 diamonds and 2 spades if she plays diamonds correctly. But a club lead will get the defense off on the right foot.|
